DESCRIPTION
Expose structured gate reviewer records in run inspection output. Users should be able to see gate rounds, reviewers, verdicts, feedback summaries, provider/model/harness, and aggregate pass/fail without opening raw artifact blobs or bead notes.

Acceptance:
- run show prints gate attempts in chronological/phase order
- per-seat lines include verdict plus provider/model/harness where present
- omitted gate data remains silent for legacy runs
- output is deterministic and documented
- tests cover multi-round gates, failures/malfunctions, and missing optional fields

DESIGN
## Plan

**Approach:** Extend `printRunDetail` in `internal/cli/run.go` to render a gates
section after the stages loop, only when `len(m.Gates) > 0` (so v0/v2 runs and any
zero-gate run print byte-identically to today — no empty header). Match the existing
flat `fmt.Fprintf` + two-space-indent idiom used for stages exactly (no tabwriter;
that is only used by `run list`). Render gates in manifest/append order (the order
capture-gate wrote them, which is already chronological per (phase, round)); do not
re-sort. Keep it a readable, scannable summary: status/tier/reviewed-stages on the
gate header lines, one block per seat with provider/model/harness + verdict, and
required-feedback bullets + failure_note + degraded/escalation reasons only when
present. No `--json`, no verbosity flag (out of scope). Provider/model/harness are
always set on seats per the schema (validateSeat requires harness.name + provider),
so render them unconditionally; required/optional/failure_note/decision reasons are
optional and printed only when non-empty.

Chosen rendering (one gate, mirrors the plan.r1 fixture):

```
gate: plan.r1
  phase:    plan
  round:    1
  tier:     2
  status:   rerun
  reviewed: plan (role=plan)
  degraded: pilms reproducible 0-CPU hang; resolved on rerun
  seat: gemini
    provider: google / gemini-3.1-pro-preview
    harness:  gemini-cli 3.1
    verdict:  block
    required:
      - backfilling old run != AC#4 new-run
      - test ref-mutating push script in throwaway repo first
      - verify local append before push
  seat: opus
    provider: anthropic / claude-opus-4-7
    harness:  claude-code opus-4-7
    verdict:  go
  seat: pilms
    provider: lmstudio / qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b
    harness:  pi x
    verdict:  disregarded
    note:     0-CPU client hang; LM Studio backend healthy
```

Rules per element:
- Gate header: `\ngate: <gate_id>` then indented `phase`, `round`, `tier`, `status`.
- `reviewed:` one line per ReviewedRef as `<stage>` plus ` (role=<role>)` when Role
  set and ` (artifact=<sha>)` when Artifact set; omit empties.
- Decision: print `escalation:` when EscalationReason set, `degraded:` when
  DegradedReason set, `deferred:` (comma-joined) when DeferredBeads non-empty;
  skip the whole block when GateDecision is zero-valued.
- Per seat: `  seat: <seat>`, then `provider: <name> / <model>`, `harness:
  <name> <version>` (drop trailing space when version empty, like the stage harness
  line). `model:` is NOT added separately (provider already carries it). `skill: <id>`
  IS rendered conditionally when `SeatResult.Skill.ID` is non-empty (a reviewer seat
  may carry a skill/tool identity; raw model seats like the dogfood reviewers usually
  leave it empty, so the line is omitted then — mirrors how the stage block treats an
  empty skill and how `note:`/`raw_output:` are conditional). Then `verdict: <verdict>`;
  `required:`/`optional:` as ` - ` bulleted sub-lists only when non-empty;
  `note: <failure_note>` only when set; `raw_output: <path>` only when RawOutput != nil
  (summarized as the artifact path, not dumped inline).

**Files:**
- `internal/cli/run.go` - add a gates section to `printRunDetail` after the
  `for _, stage := range m.Stages` loop, guarded by `if len(m.Gates) > 0`. Add one
  small helper (e.g. `printGate`) kept in the same file/style; no new imports needed
  (uses existing `fmt`/`strings`; `strings.Join` for deferred beads / reviewed roles).
- `internal/cli/run_test.go` - add tests (below). No other files change.

**Tests:** (table/standalone Go tests in run_test.go; build a v3 manifest with gates
and capture stdout via the existing `execute(...)` helper — seed it directly through
`refstore`/`runmanifest.Writer` the way `seedRunWithBadManifest`/capture helpers do,
since `capture-gate` is a separate command and these are cli-package tests)
- `TestRunShowRendersGates`: v3 run with a multi-round, multi-seat gate set
  (model the 3-gate fixture: a `rerun` round with `block` verdicts + `required`
  bullets + a `disregarded` seat with `failure_note` + `degraded_reason`, then a
  `pass` round). Assert: `gate: plan.r1` and `gate: plan.r2` headers present and in
  manifest order (idx plan.r1 < plan.r2 < implement.r1); `status:   rerun` /
  `status:   pass`; per-seat `verdict:  block`/`go`/`disregarded`; a `required:`
  bullet line; the `note:` for the disregarded seat; the `degraded:` reason;
  `provider:` shows name/model and `harness:` shows name/version.
- `TestRunShowNoGatesUnchanged`: a v2/legacy run (zero gates) must print NO `gate:`
  header and NO `gates`-related lines (assert `!strings.Contains(stdout, "gate:")`),
  proving backward-compat silence. (The existing TestRunShowExistingRun already
  pins the no-gates baseline; this adds an explicit negative assertion.)
- Edge cases covered by the fixture-shaped test: optional fields absent (go seats
  with no required/note), present (block + required, disregarded + note), and
  decision reasons (degraded). Escalated/raw_output paths are exercised lightly or
  noted as low-risk (schema-validated elsewhere). Explicitly assert a `go` seat
  prints NO `note:` line (failure_note is forbidden on go/block) and a seat with a
  non-empty Skill renders a `skill:` line while a seat with empty Skill does not.
- Verify (manual, built binary): `go build -o /tmp/etude ./cmd/etude` then
  `/tmp/etude run show etude-roadmap.2.4` and confirm the 3 gates (plan.r1 rerun,
  plan.r2 pass, implement.r1 pass) now render with all four seats incl. the
  disregarded `pilms` seat, and that the pre-existing stages output is unchanged.

**Docs:** No docs change in this bead. User-facing docs (docs/run.md) are explicitly
owned by sibling bead etude-roadmap.2.6 ("Document gate reviewer visibility"), which
depends on this one. The generated CLI reference docs/cli/etude_run_show.md is
derived from cobra `--help`; this bead adds no flags and changes no Short/Use text,
so `make docs` would produce no diff — it is intentionally not touched.

**Risks:** Low. Isolated, additive change to one print function behind a
`len(m.Gates) > 0` guard, so legacy runs are provably unaffected. Only judgment call
is the exact text layout (alignment/labels) — chosen to mirror the stage block. No
new dependencies, no schema/capture changes.

